com/mov/demon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Melee up comming changes.. (cant find any funny title)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> see these changes as a good thing. Every other class in the game has to work at not getting aggro or keeping aggro, yes even knights. Casting heals at just the right time, with lag can be difficult. Making sure slows or debuffs are cast at the right time all require pushing buttons at the right time. Why shouldn't warriors have to do the same thing?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Warriors already have to know when to push what button at the right time.<br>
<br>
Have to know when to taunt. You dont just push it each time it comes up. That's a waste.<br>
<br>
If your like me you use disarm as well for the extra hate it generates.<br>
<br>
Have to know when to kick/bash/slam. This is to interupt casting and that is a real pain when you dont have effects on due to lag.<br>
<br>
Have to know when to cut your attacks so you dont get wiped by an enrage. That can wipe a raid fast when that happens.<br>
<br>
Have to know when to use your Defensive disk. <br>
<br>
You also should  be ready to switch weapons quickly and know when to do it.<br>
<br>
Not to mention watching your buffs and useing click gear when needed. That often requires switching gear out while in a fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
And on top of all that we are normaly in charge of positioning the mob. This is etreamly hard to do when everyone has  a knock back of some type.<br>
<br>
People think all we do is click taunt every 10 seconds and it simply isn't true. I do more clciking on my warrior then any of my casters. The only charecter I have that requires more is my bard and I can make a macro that handles most of that so in truth not really.<br>
<br>
The problem with the changes as they are stated does not say &quot;FIX&quot; to me. It sounds like glossing over and adding more clicks that we don't need.<br>
<br>
